tasks.description:
Schema updates for archive metadata tracking - REVISED for multi-agent/multi-user future.

## New Fields in Archived Task

### archivedBy (NEW - Multi-Agent/Multi-User Attribution)
```json
{
  "archivedBy": {
    "type": "string",
    "enum": ["user", "agent", "auto", "hook"],
    "description": "Actor type that performed the archive"
  },
  "archivedByIdentity": {
    "type": "string",
    "description": "Actor identity: git user, session ID, or policy name"
  },
  "archivedByGitUser": {
    "type": "string",
    "description": "Git user identity if available (e.g., 'Name <email>')"
  }
}
```

### archivedFrom (REVISED - Git Context)
```json
{
  "archivedFromBranch": {
    "type": "string",
    "description": "Git branch name at archive time"
  },
  "archivedFromCommit": {
    "type": "string",
    "description": "Git commit SHA at archive time"
  }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] archivedBy* fields added to archive schema
- [ ] archivedFrom* git context fields added
- [ ] archive.sh populates fields from git config and session
- [ ] Backward compatible (new fields optional)

## Future Value
- Multi-agent session tracking
- Multi-user collaboration audit trail
- Git-integrated task management provenance
